Inventory management

Inventory management is the process of ordering, handling, storing, and selling of inventory – both of raw materials and finished goods. 
A company’s precises inventory management processes will depend on the goods or service provided. For example, a company may choose to store raw materials for the 
entire financial period or adopt a just in time (JIT) approach subject to demand. Naturally, option inventory management will help reduce costs, optimize fulfillment, 
provide better customer service and to prevent losses from theft, spoilage and returns.  
